$interpreted: Himawari: What a rocky road you've had to walk to get here.
Himawari: And yet, in the end you choose to protect your own pathetic life.
Himawari: If your own people knew, I’m sure they’d be disappointed in you.
Himawari: You trusted the princess so much, but then...
Himawari: Ah~ I almost forgot!
Himawari: They must all be so busy right now, no time to deal with you~
Tindoiimu: Sorry, are you done?
Himawari: What?
Tindoiimu: Oh, were you trying to piss me off just now? Sorry, I wasn't paying attention.
Himawari: You...!
Himawari: Hmph, might as well take the opportunity while it’s right in front of you.
Tindoiimu: Yeah? Well, thanks for reminding me, then.
Tindoiimu: If you hadn't reminded me, the Bull Tribe might already have my people surrounded by now.
Tindoiimu: And yet, I heard they set out this morning... in a different dirrection.
Himawari: Pfft, even a child could see through your lies.
Tindoiimu: It's funny, though... that one bull soldier likes you so much, wouldn't he come tell you if his men had the insects surrounded?
Tindoiimu: Really, if your crappy acting can convince them of anything, then don't you think I'd have a decent chance, too?
Himawari: Lies! What proof do you have?
Bull Soldier: All contestants can now enter the arena.
Tindoiimu: Why don't you just go ask someone from the Bull Tribe. I'm sure they'll tell you.
Himawari: Excuse me, did the Bull Tribe start advancing on the Insect Tribe this morning?
Bull Soldier: ...Uh, I heard they went somewhere else.
Himawari: B-But, how!?
Tindoiimu: Seems like it doesn’t matter who wins, everyone will come out the bad guy.
Tindoiimu: So, get the answer you were looking for?
Himawari: You... I still don’t believe a word you’ve said! What do a few soldiers know, anyway!?
Tindoiimu: Doesn’t matter if you believe it or not─
Tindoiimu: Everything’s working out as planned.
Himawari: (No way... my plan was perfect. How did she mess it up!?)
Chiyuki: The winner is... Tindoiimu!
Himawari: Dammit, it’s always you…
Himawari: Why are you always getting in my damn way!?
Himawari: If it weren’t for you, I’d be the only one for Juan-Yun!
Tindoiimu: Whatever you say.
Tindoiimu: Still, I have to thank you for your foolishness. Without you, I'd never be able to save my people... or win this tournament.
Excited Audience: Incredible! Mythics are amazing!
Water Sect Audience: Go, Soohyeon!!
Fog Sect Audience: Toyokuni!!
Toyokuni: Very good, Soohyeon! You've gotten stronger, and you're no longer hesitating!
Soohyeon: I have to give it all I’ve got, my enemy is no joke!
Toyokuni: Well then, let us both give it our all!
Soohyeon: Deal.
Toyokuni: And yet, we all know you're much more skilled than I am.
Toyokuni: And for all you've done for me... I am forever grateful.
Toyokuni: The loser must step down today... So, Soohyeon, you better not lose.
Soohyeon: I will... try my best!
